|1907
| [[Plunket Society|The Royal New Zealand Plunket Society]]
| The Plunket Society was founded by [[Truby King|Sir Frederic Truby King]] (1858-1938) to help mothers with their babies, who were dying from malnutrition and disease.<ref>[https://www.plunket.org.nz/what-we-do/who-we-are/our-history/ "Our history"], "Plunket." Retrieved 5/2/14</ref>
