|1919
| [[Edward Hunter (Billy Banjo)|Edward Hunter]] 
| A trade unionist called Edward Hunter (1885-1959) founded a group called the Rights of Childhood League, which brought together like-minded groups to lobby for an improvement to child's welfare. Hunter also published a booklet called the ''Rights of childhood''.<ref>[http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&d=MW19190312.2.9 "The Rights of Childhood"], "Papers Past - Maoriland Worker, Volume 10, Issue 418, 12 March 1919, p. 1." Retrieved 5/2/14.</ref>
